{{nihongo|'''Ubagami Daijingū'''|姥神大神宮}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Esashi, Hokkaidō (Hiyama)|Esashi]], [[Hokkaidō]], [[Japan]]. Its foundation date is uncertain but its existence is documented from the [[Edo period]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hokkaidojinjacho.jp/data/03/03001.html |title=Ubagami Daijingū |publisher=Hokkaidō Jinja-chō |accessdate=22 April 2011}}</ref> It is considered the oldest Shinto Shrine in Hokkaido.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ubagamidaijingu Shrine |url=https://en.esashi.town/tourism/page.php?id=82 |access-date=2023-04-21 |website=Portal site for Tourist information of Hokkaido Esashi Town |language=en}}</ref> The Ubagami Daijingū Togyosai, when [[Float (parade)|floats]] decked out with lanterns are paraded through the town, is celebrated in August.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hokkaido-esashi.jp/ubagami/index.htm |title=Ubagami Daijingū |publisher=[[Esashi, Hokkaidō (Hiyama)|Esashi Town]] |accessdate=22 April 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110712005903/http://www.hokkaido-esashi.jp/ubagami/index.htm |archivedate=12 July 2011 }}</ref>

