[[sn:Ubagami Daijingū]] [[en:Ubagami Daijingū]]
[[Category:Pages without translation templates]] <!--enwiki derived wikidata interwikis--> {{Commons category|Ubagami Daijin-gū}} [[fr:Ubagami Daijin-gū]] [[ja:姥神大神宮]] [[Category:pages with valid en interwikis]]

{{Short description|Shinto shrine}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}} {{Infobox religious building | name = {{nihongo|'''Ubagami Daijingū'''|姥神大神宮}} | image = Ubagami Shrine 090206.jpg | caption = Ubagami Daijingū | map_type = Japan | map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|41|51|59.2|N|140|7|30.1|E|region:JP_type:landmark|display=title,inline}} | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | type = | deity = | founded_by = | established = | date_destroyed = | location = [[Esashi, Hokkaidō (Hiyama)|Esashi]], [[Hokkaidō]], [[Japan]]. | website = | architecture_style = | festival = | leadership = }} {{nihongo|'''Ubagami Daijingū'''|姥神大神宮}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Esashi, Hokkaidō (Hiyama)|Esashi]], [[Hokkaidō]], [[Japan]]. Its foundation date is uncertain but its existence is documented from the [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hokkaidojinjacho.jp/data/03/03001.html |title=Ubagami Daijingū |publisher=Hokkaidō Jinja-chō |accessdate=22 April 2011}}</ref> It is considered the oldest Shinto Shrine in Hokkaido.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ubagamidaijingu Shrine |url=https://en.esashi.town/tourism/page.php?id=82 |access-date=2023-04-21 |website=Portal site for Tourist information of Hokkaido Esashi Town |language=en}}</ref> The Ubagami Daijingū Togyosai, when [[:en:Float (parade)|floats]] decked out with lanterns are paraded through the town, is celebrated in August.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hokkaido-esashi.jp/ubagami/index.htm |title=Ubagami Daijingū |publisher=[[Esashi, Hokkaidō (Hiyama)|Esashi Town]] |accessdate=22 April 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110712005903/http://www.hokkaido-esashi.jp/ubagami/index.htm |archivedate=12 July 2011 }}</ref>
